cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with distributed algorithms for load balancing, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of randomized algorithms and information theory concepts suggests a possible fit with cs.IT. The application of the algorithm to a fully connected graph with message passing also suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (networking and internet architecture) and cs.SY (systems and control).
